==English==

===Noun===
'''[[double]] [[bluff]]'''
# A double bluff is where you want people to think you're bluffing, but in fact you're bluffing the bluff, and actually are speaking the truth. 

====Example====
You have a 3 and a 7 in poker. You raise by a big amount, saying "Hey, you're probably going to win the round, I've just got a 3 and a 7, but I'll raise anyway"

